    "causal_summary": "Two recent investigation packets (005 defects catalog and 006 cross-AI stress-test) surfaced a coherent set of MCP runtime defects spanning the memory layer, code graph, cocoindex mirror handling, intent classifier, and a new model-side hallucination class on weak retrieval signals. Source patches were claimed as landed for several P0 fixes, yet live MCP probes continue to show pre-fix behavior — implying phantom fixes (source compiled but not built into dist or daemon not restarted). A focused, autonomous, multi-iteration root cause and remediation investigation is required before scattered point fixes are attempted.",
